        // "exhibit_2_explain_name_1" : "The Origin of All Beginnings",
        "exhibit_2_explain_1" : "The University Collaboration Exhibition showcases the creativity and experimental vision of university students who represent the future of media art. Through works that reinterpret everyday life in Seoul, the changing seasons, tradition and modernity, as well as personal memories and emotions, the exhibition creates new opportunities for connection and empathy between young artists and the public through a civic media art platform.",
        // "exhibit_2_explain_name_2" : "Moment Seoul",
        "exhibit_2_explain_2" : "The Nature Project Exhibition explores the vitality of nature, the passage of time, and the values of renewal and cyclical change. Addressing themes such as the changing seasons, ecological restoration, everyday observations of nature, and the interconnectedness between microscopic life and the vast universe, the featured works offer diverse perspectives on the natural world while inviting visitors to pause, reflect, and contemplate.",
